TITLE: Treasured Friendship
INSIDEVERSE:
Personalize the gift of a book. or create your own Bookmark. with an inspirational saying or a favorite recipe. Bookmarks are the perfect way to express yourself.

You'll Need:

Paper. 8 1/2 x 11 inches. Scissors.

Directions:

  1. Click on Personalize and Print Your Project to open the Creative workspace.
  2. Make text changes as desired.
  3. Click Print Project to send finished Bookmark to the printer.
  4. Cut along outside edges.

Tips:

Print your project on scrap paper first to check the alignment. spelling. and overall look of the project. Use craft scissors to cut the edges with fun designs. Laminate your bookmark with self-adhesive plastic. Punch a hole at the top and attach a tassel or ribbon.

TITLE: Sunny Day
INSIDEVERSE:
Coloring Sheets are a great activity for kids. just about anytime and anywhere. whether it’s in the classroom. at home on a rainy afternoon.

You'll Need: Paper. 8 1/2 x 11 inches. Crayons or washable markers.

Directions:

  1. Click Personalize and Print Your Project to open the Creative Workspace.
  2. Make text changes as desired.
  3. Click Print Project to send finished Coloring Sheet to the printer.


Tips:

Print your project on scrap paper first to check the alignment. spelling. and overall look of the project. Enhance the completed coloring sheet with glitter paint or stickers. Give kids crayons (or washable markers) and a coloring sheet. and watch their creativity come to life!

TITLE: Special Gift
INSIDEVERSE:
Creat & Print special Coupon Books for an extra special gift.

You'll Need:

Paper. 8 1/2 x 11 inches. preferably card stock. Scissors. Staples and stapler. or hole punch and string or yarn.

Directions:
  1. Click on Personalize and Print Your Project to open the Creative workspace.
  2. Personalize the text. Select the text to write over it or to change size. color. and font style.
  3. Click Print Project to send finished Coupons to the printer.
  4. Cut out coupon cover and each coupon.
  5. Stack coupons and cover in a neat pile. with coupon cover on top.
  6. If using staples to bind coupons and cover together. staple coupons and cover along the left side of the pile.
  7. If using string to bind coupons and cover together. punch three holes along the left side of the pile. and thread and tie string or yarn through each hole.
Tips:

Print your project on scrap paper first to check the alignment. spelling. and overall look of the project.

TITLE: Pretty Fan
INSIDEVERSE:
Add your own special whimsy and charm to all your gifts. whether they're wrapped in boxes or bags. Personalized package decorations add warmth to every occasion.

You'll Need:

Paper. 8 1/2 x 11 inches. Scissors. Glue or tape.

Directions:

  1. Click on Personalize and Print Your Project to open the Creative workspace.
  2. Make text changes as desired.
  3. Click Print Project to send finished Package Decoration to the printer.
  4. Cut along the solid. exterior lines. cutting out all design pieces.
  5. Glue or tape back panel to reverse side of front panel.
  6. Fold along dotted lines.
  7. Carefully cut out the hole at the bottom center of the fan.
  8. Tie a string or ribbon through the hole.
  9. Attach completed Package Decoration to the present or bag handle.

Tips:

Print your project on scrap paper first to check the alignment. spelling. and overall look of the project. Enhance the design with glitter paint or stickers.

TITLE: Just for...
INSIDEVERSE:
Add your own special whimsy and charm to all your gifts. whether they're wrapped in boxes or bags. Personalized package decorations add warmth to every occasion.

You'll Need:

Paper. 8 1/2 x 11 inches. Scissors. Tape or glue.

Directions:

  1. Click on Personalize and Print Your Project to open the Creative workspace.
  2. Make text changes as desired.
  3. Click Print Project to send finished Package Decoration to the printer.
  4. Cut along the solid. exterior lines. cutting out all design pieces. Cut slits along solid. interior lines on base piece.
  5. Position matching face piece on top of the base piece. Then. fold at dotted lines on tabs at the side of the face piece.
  6. Insert face piece tabs into slits on the base piece. If needed. use tape or glue to secure tabs to back of base piece.
  7. Carefully cut out the hole to the right of the dog's tale.
  8. Tie a string or ribbon through the hole.
  9. Attach completed Package Decoration to the present or bag handle.

Tips:

Print your project on scrap paper first to check the alignment. spelling. and overall look of the project. Enhance the design with glitter paint or stickers.
